                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-18T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 18, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5788. Your 6340, November 11 and previous. Tehran telegram 375 November 14 reads,
                    in part, as follows:</p>
                <pb facs="0213" n="201" xml:id="pg_201"/>
                <p>[Here follows text of first two paragraphs of telegram No. 375, printed on <ref
                        target="#pg_195">page 195</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Please ask Foreign Office to give urgent consideration to possible immediate
                    shipment of wheat from India or Middle East, rather than North America. Quantity
                    furnished to meet Iranian emergency could, of course, be replaced later by
                    shipments from this loading area.</p>
                <p>We are asking New Delhi to make inquiry in this regard of the Government of
                    India.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
